{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id14b0b93a-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s871a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"871a"},"text":"§ 871a.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Semiannual reports to Congress","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id14b0b93b-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s871a/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" In general","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The Attorney General shall, on a semiannual basis, submit to the congressional committees and organizations specified in subsection (b) reports that—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id14b0b93c-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s871a/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" describe the allocation of the resources of the Drug Enforcement Administration and the Federal Bureau of Investigation for the investigation and prosecution of alleged violations of the Controlled Substances Act [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s801"},"text":"21 U.S.C. 801","children":[],"tail":" et seq.] involving methamphetamine; and"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id14b0b93d-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s871a/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" the measures being taken to give priority in the allocation of such resources to such violations involving—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id14b0b93e-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s871a/a/2/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" persons alleged to have imported into the United States substantial quantities of methamphetamine or scheduled listed chemicals (as defined pursuant to the amendment made by section 711(a)(1)); ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn002161"},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"type":"footnote","id":"fn002161"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":" See References in Text note below."}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id14b0b93f-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s871a/a/2/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" persons alleged to have manufactured methamphetamine; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id14b0b940-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s871a/a/2/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" circumstances in which the violations have endangered children.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id14b0b941-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s871a/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Congressional committees","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The congressional committees and organizations referred to in subsection (a) are—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id14b0b942-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s871a/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" in the House of Representatives, the Committee on the Judiciary, the Committee on Energy and Commerce, and the Committee on Government Reform; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id14b0b943-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s871a/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" in the Senate, the Committee on the Judiciary, the Committee on Commerce, Science, and Transportation, and the Caucus on International Narcotics Control.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id14b0b944-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/177/tVII/s736"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–177, title VII, § 736","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2006-03-09"},"text":"Mar. 9, 2006","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/120/271"},"text":"120 Stat. 271","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id14b0b945-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id14b0b946-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id14b0b947-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Controlled Substances Act, referred to in subsec. (a)(1), is title II of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/513"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–513","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1970-10-27"},"text":"Oct. 27, 1970","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/84/1242"},"text":"84 Stat. 1242","children":[],"tail":", which is classified principally to this subchapter. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s801"},"text":"section 801 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section 711(a)(1), referred to in subsec. (a)(2)(A), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/177/s711/a/1"},"text":"section 711(a)(1) of Pub. L. 109–177","children":[],"tail":", which amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s802"},"text":"section 802 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"id14b0b948-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was enacted as part of the USA PATRIOT Improvement and Reauthorization Act of 2005 and also as part of the Combat Methamphetamine Epidemic Act of 2005, and not as part of the Controlled Substances Act which comprises this subchapter.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id14b0b949-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"changeOfName","id":"id14b0b94a-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Change of Name","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Committee on Government Reform of House of Representatives changed to Committee on Oversight and Government Reform of House of Representatives by House Resolution No. 6, One Hundred Tenth Congress, ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2007-01-05"},"text":"Jan. 5, 2007","children":[],"tail":". Committee on Oversight and Government Reform of House of Representatives changed to Committee on Oversight and Reform of House of Representatives by House Resolution No. 6, One Hundred Sixteenth Congress, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2019-01-09"},"text":"Jan. 9, 2019","children":[],"tail":". Committee on Oversight and Reform of House of Representatives changed to Committee on Oversight and Accountability of House of Representatives by House Resolution No. 5, One Hundred Eighteenth Congress, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2023-01-09"},"text":"Jan. 9, 2023","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
